Colombia Stocks: Canacol, Ecopetrol, Rubiales Rise; Aval Falls

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-02T15:52:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/colombia-stocks-canacol-ecopetrol-rubiales-rise-aval-falls.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:24 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.5 percent to 14,462.39, while the
Colcap Index gained 0.4 percent to 1,706.82, as stocks advanced
after U.S. forces killed al-Qaeda leader Osama Bin Laden.  Oil companies  rose as crude jumped to the highest level
since September 2008 amid concern that the death of Osama bin
Laden will spur retaliatory attacks that could disrupt supplies.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based oil
company that operates fields in South America, was set to gain
for a fifth consecutive day after falling a record 18 percent on
April 25. The stock rose 2.3 percent to 2,420 pesos.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 1.6 percent to 3,860 pesos.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)   rose 1.1 percent to
54,000 pesos, its highest intraday level since April 20.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA,  Colombia ’s
biggest financial holding company, fell 0.7 percent to 1,340
pesos as investors waited for delayed results of the company’s
share issue, said Mauricio Restrepo Del Toro, research director
at brokerage Bolsa y Renta.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
